subSubSection.paragraph:
ABDOMEN. Tergites glabrous or sparsely tomentose; colour chequered yellow/black in adults (
Fig. 15D
), the black being predominant and giving the insect a dark look. A thin, pale median line along the whole length of the insect is generally present.
